$$$ File Mangement – Nimble Commander

? Website

, @||@ { !https://magnumbytes.com/ }

? Repo

, @||@ { !https://github.com/mikekazakov/nimble-commander }

? License

, @| '| GNU General Public License, Version 3.0 |' |@ { !https://github.com/mikekazakov/nimble-commander/blob/master/LICENSE }

A two­‑pane, keyboard­‑navigable file browser.
I find this easier to work in for project directories with potentially lots of folders or files than Finder, and the ability to set a shortcut to open a file in a text editor instead of its default app is extremely handy.
I use the free version available through the Mac App Store and have no complaints.

$$$ Keyboard Layout Customization – Ukelele

? Website

, @||@ { !https://software.sil.org/ukelele/ }

? Repo

, @||@ { !https://github.com/sillsdev/Ukelele }

? License

, All rights reserved.

macOS has the best custom keyboard support of any operating system, but you wouldnʼt know it without downloading Ukelele, provided by SIL.
Everything I type these days is written on a custom keyboard configured to my uses, and all of my custom keyboards start out being created with Ukelele.

